abstract: Mr. Biden’s fund-raising haul fell short of Pete Buttigieg’s total for the second quarter of the year, though Mr. Biden did not enter the race until late April.
snippet: Mr. Biden’s fund-raising haul fell short of Pete Buttigieg’s total for the second quarter of the year, though Mr. Biden did not enter the race until late April.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has raised $21.5 million since entering the presidential race in late April, his campaign said Wednesday.

snippet: ‘Medicare for all’ would essentially do away with private insurance, a fact that some politicians seem reluctant to emphasize.
lead_paragraph: The Medicare for All Act written by Senator Bernie Sanders would cover not just standard medical services, but also vision, dental and long-term care. It would offer more health benefits than the world’s leading universal health care systems.

abstract: But has he raised the political temperature too high for his own good?
snippet: But has he raised the political temperature too high for his own good?
lead_paragraph: For Democrats seeking to pry loose moderates and conservatives in 2020, the voters drawn to President Trump by their shared animosity to all things liberal are an impenetrable constituency, long gone, while more traditional Republicans offer the potential for modest support.

abstract: Female candidates are climbing in the polls and dominating debates. Yet Democrats are still being asked if a woman can be elected president.

headline_main: It’s a Question No One Says They Want to Ask. But the Women Running for President Keep Hearing It.
headline_print_headline: Six Female Candidates, One Unrelenting Refrain

abstract: Fourteen candidates are assured a place onstage. The rest are battling it out for six remaining slots. In September, things get tougher.
snippet: Fourteen candidates are assured a place onstage. The rest are battling it out for six remaining slots. In September, things get tougher.
lead_paragraph: With just four weeks to go until the second set of Democratic presidential primary debates, a handful of lower-tier candidates are in danger of missing them. A single percentage point of support in one poll could be the difference between getting invited to Detroit and being left off the debate stage.
